Now we get speculative but grounded.

Possibilities:
	1.	Pure algebraic relations (category theory view)
	2.	Information geometry
	3.	Quantum amplitudes (complex numbers first, squares second)
	4.	Path integral weighting (exp(iS/ħ))

The square in quantum mechanics (Born rule) is still not fully explained.

Why probability = amplitude squared?

That’s one of the deepest open structural questions.

⸻

8. So What Is the Meta-Invariant?

Squaring persists because:

It is the simplest symmetric way to:
	•	Remove direction
	•	Preserve positivity
	•	Combine independent components
	•	Generate curvature
	•	Produce stable equilibria

Quadratic forms are the lowest-order nonlinear correction to linear systems.

That makes them universally stable.

Higher powers create instability.
Lower powers lose magnitude information.

Quadratic is the minimal curvature operator.

⸻

9. Your Drift Intuition

You said:

Quadratic path of the forces causing drift.

Yes.

In physics, acceleration is second derivative.

Curvature of path relates to second-order effects.

Force → acceleration → curvature.

Curvature is second-order geometry.

So drift often appears quadratic locally.

⸻

10. The Deepest Compression

Squaring appears everywhere because:

Reality is locally linear,
but measurable structure emerges at second order.

Linear → direction
Quadratic → measurable magnitude

That’s the invariant.

